				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Interesting alternative.<br /><br /><br />I don't consider <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Detect_TV_system" class="postlink">tepples' NTSC/PAL detection on the wiki</a> an addition to my NMI routine though. All of that code is outside the NMI, it just requires that your NMI handler:<br />1. Increments a frame counter variable.<br />2. Can finish in under 1500 cycles (doesn't have to always, just requires that it can).<br /><br />Every NMI handler I've written has needed to meet these requirements whether or not I wanted to use the detection code, so there's never been any loss/complexity in the handler to support tepples' detector.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

