				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Here's the detection code I added for the the NROM port of Driar:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;;; the &quot;nice&quot; thing is that I'm using the PPU power-on wait to detect the video system-<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;; A,X,Y are all 0 at entry<br />@vwait1:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bit $2002<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bpl @vwait1&nbsp; ; at this point, about 27384 cycles have passed<br />@vwait2:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; inx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bne @noincy<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; iny<br />@noincy:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bit $2002<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bpl @vwait2&nbsp; ; at this point, about 57165 cycles have passed<br /><br />;;; BUT because of a hardware oversight, we might have missed a vblank flag.<br />;;;&nbsp; so we need to both check for 1Vbl and 2Vbl<br />;;; NTSC NES: 29780 cycles / 12.005 -&gt; $9B0 or $1361 (Y:X)<br />;;; PAL NES:&nbsp; 33247 cycles / 12.005 -&gt; $AD1 or $15A2<br />;;; Dendy:&nbsp; &nbsp; 35464 cycles / 12.005 -&gt; $B8A or $1714<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; tya<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; cmp #16<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bcc @nodiv2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; lsr<br />@nodiv2:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; clc<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; adc #&lt;-9<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; cmp #3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bcc @noclip3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; lda #3<br />@noclip3:<br />;;; Right now, A contains 0,1,2,3 for NTSC,PAL,Dendy,Bad<br /></div>Modifying Driar's NMI was out of scope, so (like you) I wanted a NMI-less solution.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

